benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{email} - Delete email from account

covered: Valid Deletion: Multiple scenarios demonstrate successful deletion (TC01, TC02, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC17, TC18, TC19).
Non-Existent Resource: Tests for non-existent account (TC03) and non-existent email (TC04, TC09).
Invalid Input Handling: Invalid accountId format (TC05) and invalid email format (TC06); missing required header (TC07); XSS/injection attempt (TC16).
Authorization/Authentication: Tests for missing/invalid token (TC10) and required header presence (TC07).
Additional Robustness: Optional headers (TC02), extra parameters (TC08), large/minimal email lengths (TC12, TC13), performance (TC14).
Resilience/Recovery: System error (TC11) and transient network failure recovery (TC19).
gaps: Caching and headers: No tests asserting caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) or explicit cache-related responses.
Rate limiting: No tests simulating burst or throttling under high load.
Pagination: Not applicable to DELETE single-resource in this context, but guideline mentions for list endpoints; no pagination scenarios exist (acceptable).
Soft-delete behavior: No explicit check whether deletion is soft (logical) vs hard delete; tests assume deletion is final but do not verify any soft-delete flag or archival behavior.
recommendations: Add tests to verify caching headers on deletion responses (ETag/Cache-Control) and ensure clients handle them correctly.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to confirm proper handling under high request volumes.
If applicable, include a test to confirm whether deletions are soft or hard and verify any archival/soft-delete indicators if the API supports them.
